==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Old English [[misteltan|misteltān]], from [[mistel]] ‘mistletoe’ + [[tan#Old English|tān]] ‘twig’.  Compare [[mistle]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmɪsəltəʊ/}}

===Noun===
'''mistletoe'''

#<!--Viscum_album--><!--Phoradendron_leucarpum-->A parasitic [[evergreen]] plant with white [[berry|berries]] that grows on [[oak]]s, apple trees and other trees.

====Usage notes====
#The term '''mistletoe''' is used for both ''[[Viscum album]]'' ([[European mistletoe]]) and ''[[Phoradendron leucarpum]]'' ([[Eastern mistletoe]]).

